news.title: Promoters must name the projects as per sanctioned maps: UP-RERA
news.para: It was also observed that promoters were using project brand names which were different from the names registered with RERA and this was creating doubts amongst the existing and prospective home buyers.

news.title: Bokaro Steel plans mapping exercise to flush out illegal occupants from residential quarters
news.para: Only last year, the BSL management recorded that nearly 1,300 of its quarters were illegally occupied. However, the PSU estimates that the number of illegally occupied quarters could be well beyond 3,000.

news.title: Submit stability certificate for alterations in Chandigarh housing board homes
news.para: Residents of Sectors 41A, 41D, 45C, 45D, 46, 47C, 39B and 29B have been asked to get the structural stability of their dwelling units assessed from the structural engineers empanelled with the Chandigarh administration for the additions/alterations carried out by them and submit the certificate to the Chandigarh Housing Board at their own cost.

news.title: Promoters must prove legal title on the project land: UP-RERA
news.para: RERA has also directed the promoters to file an affidavit to the effect that the project land is free from encumbrances and to disclose the same if there is any encumbrance on the land of the project.

news.title: Real estate investors in Europe turn to lawyers after 'huge' CO₂ shock
news.para: Property owners across the region will need to invest vast sums in renovations to ensure their buildings aren't emitting illegal levels of carbon dioxide or consuming excessive amounts of energy, according to lawyers advising the sector.

news.title: High Court urges swift appointment of Karnataka REAT chairperson
news.para: However, the High Court has directed the State to initiate the process of identifying and appointing a member to fill the ensuing vacancy and also the constitution of the Tribunal without any delay.

news.title: Gurugram: Chintels Paradiso buyers flag concerns over redevelopment
news.para: In a meeting held on Sunday, residents alleged that the agreement is “one-sided in nature”, which they felt did not represent their interests fairly.

news.title: Rainwater harvesting a necessity as high-rises stare at crisis: Expert
news.para: Highlighting the cyclical issues of drought, water shortage and eventually urban flooding, she noted that Hyderabad has gone from being traditionally water abundant to water scarce city.

news.title: How safe are highrises? Fire in Bhubaneswar reignites concerns
news.para: According to the Agnisama Seva portal, four major fire divisions of the city have received 1,095 applications for fire safety certificates so far out of which approval has been given to only 467 buildings, which is less than 50% of the applications.

news.title: Collect plot cost from allottee: Telangana HC
news.para: Since she had already paid ₹6,000 per square metre, the balance amount should be collected from her, the court said.

news.title: Karnataka RERA yet to recover Rs 486 crore as penalty from builders
news.para: So far, in the last seven years, K-RERA has imposed a penalty in 1,248 cases and the penalty amount added up to Rs 547.31 crore. Till now, penalty has been collected in 138 cases and the total penalty collected is Rs 60.64 crore. It is yet to recover Rs 486.68 crore from 1,110 pending cases.​​

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body to apply new jantri rates for plots on temporary lease
news.para: However, with the new policy, the AMC will apply the revised jantri rates to these temporary leases, with a 25% concession on rent for plots used for commercial purposes.

news.title: Gujarat HC orders dissenters to vacate flats for redevelopment
news.para: Buildings in the Shilpalaya Co-operative Housing Society, constructed in the mid-1980s, are severely damaged, prompting residents to initiate the redevelopment process in 2014.

news.title: Follow rules on local use of sand: Telangana government to district administrations
news.para: District officials have been told to follow the instructions/ guidelines issued from time to time with regard to regulation of sand extraction and availability for local utilization.

news.title: Haryana RERA forfeits security deposits of 20 builders for non-compliance with registration norms
news.para: ​The real estate promoters had been granted conditional project registration certificates. The promoters, however, failed to meet the conditions within the stipulated time, leading to violations, a RERA (Gurgaon) order said.

news.title: Kolkata civic body forms committee to probe Garden Reach building collapse
news.para: The seven-member committee will be headed by the KMC joint municipal commissioner and will also have representatives of the Kolkata Police, the order said.

news.title: Plans in place to maximise collection of property tax in Delhi
news.para: Till Friday, MCD’s property tax collection was Rs 1,950 crore in comparison to Rs 1,862 crore till this point of time last year. The overall collection last year was Rs 2,417 crore.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Consumer commission orders society to compensate for not transferring share certificates
news.para: The Consumer Dispute Redressal Commission, Ahmedabad (rural) also ordered the society to transfer the share certificates to the complainant’s name, as the society had already accepted the transfer fee.

news.title: FIRs against seven developers of illegal colonies in Ludhiana
news.para: According to the information, three FIRs were registered against three unidentified developers for developing an unauthorised colony at Dehlon village and two at Khanpur village.

news.title: GCC share in commercial real estate is on the rise
news.para: The firm says GCCs - technology and shared services arms of MNCs - have become a significant part of commercial real estate since the pandemic. In the decade prior to that, IT firms dominated.
